# Qordy project context

**Root:** `/var/www/vhosts/qordy.com`

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| PHP backend | `httpdocs/` (`httpdocs/app/` application code) |
| Flutter web mobile | `flutter_app/` → built to `httpdocs/public/mobile-app/` |
| Database / env | `httpdocs/.env` (local credentials; never commit) |

## Agent brief

Read [`CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md) for active tasks, tenant/subdomain repair, smoke checks, PHP/Flutter build commands, and completion criteria.

## Audits and deep reviews

When the user asks for **audit**, **architecture review**, **security review**, **performance review**, **codebase analysis**, or similar:

1. Read [`AUDIT.md`](../../AUDIT.md) first (analysis before changes; reports to `docs/audit/`).
2. Prefer enabling the **audit-directive** Cursor rule or `@AUDIT.md` in the prompt for full discipline.

Do not mix audit reports into CLAUDE.md unless the user requests it.

## Conventions

- Use central services (`DependencyFactory`, `NavigationService`); avoid mock/hardcoded production data.
- Minimal diffs; match existing patterns.
- No commits/push unless the user asks.
- Live chat / in-app support was removed — do not reintroduce without explicit request.
